```json
{
"application": "Slurm",
"software": [
"Singularity",
"TensorFlow",
"HAProxy",
"Python",
"nvidia-smi",
"lsof",
"date",
"mkdir",
"cd",
"module",
"cms",
"seff"
],
"resources": [
"GPU (NVIDIA V100)",
"CPU",
"Memory (48GB per GPU)",
"Network",
"Disk (local scratch)",
"Slurm cluster"
]
}
```

This script runs on the Slurm workload manager, which is a common tool for managing high-performance computing resources. The script utilizes several other software packages, including Singularity, TensorFlow, HAProxy, Python, and various system utilities. The script leverages GPU resources (NVIDIA V100) along with CPU and memory, and it interacts with the local scratch disk and the network. The script also utilizes Slurm's resource management capabilities for managing nodes, tasks, time, and other resources.
